Here is the exact, complete data flow and system architecture mapped directly from your codebase.

## High-Level Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant UI as Next.js Frontend
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant Graph as LangGraph (Agent Core)
    participant DB as MongoDB Atlas
    participant Tools as Tools & External APIs

    U->>UI: Types message & clicks Send
    UI->>API: POST /api/chat (JSON payload)
    API->>DB: Fetch existing Chat History (if conversation_id exists)
    DB-->>API: Returns history
    API->>Graph: Invoke StateGraph with User Message
    
    loop ReAct Loop (Reasoning + Acting)
        Graph->>Graph: LLM evaluates context
        alt Tool Call Required
            Graph->>Tools: Execute Built-in or MCP Tool
            Tools-->>Graph: Return Tool Output
        else Final Answer
            Graph->>Graph: Generate Final Output
        end
    end
    
    Graph-->>API: Returns Final Response String
    API->>DB: Save updated Conversation (with 30-Day TTL)
    API-->>UI: HTTP 200 (JSON Response)
    UI->>U: Renders Markdown Output
```

